column4: "full_text": "Is this bill perfect? No. But overall this legislation improves how our country performs its most critical work. #HR1 (14/14)"
column27: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "The bill would create nonpartisan
column5: independent commissions for each state. You\u2019re supposed to choose us
column6: not the other way around. We shouldn\u2019t let politicians pick and choose which voters get to elect them. #HR1 (13/)"
column29: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "We want to make sure that your voice is just as important as anyone else\u2019s
column5: regardless of how much or how little you have. #HR1 (12/)"
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "This bill would make sure that you can know who is paying for ads you see on TV or Facebook or Twitter. That Is often a secret now! This would keep foreign-controlled companies from making large donations. #HR1 (11/)"
column27: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "I don\u2019t see that requirement as a burden. I\u2019m happy to disclose our donors and expenditures. Dark money groups don\u2019t have to tell you where they got their money
column5: who gave it to them or how they spent it. They shouldn\u2019t get special protections. #HR1 (10/)"
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "I have heard it all across my district: We need to change how Washington works. Outside groups spend billions of dollars to sway policy here. And although members of congress have to disclose every dollar that flows into our campaign accounts
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "The bill authorizes $1 billion to help states strengthen their security systems. Is that a lot of money? Yes. But again
column5: election access and security are key to our democracy. #HR1 (8/)"
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "We must also ensure our voting systems are secure. Although OK's voter access could improve
column5: our system sets an example for the rest of the country. It is consistent statewide
column6: uses easy-to-read paper ballots and machines that have never been connected to the internet. #HR1 (7/)"
column29: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "Voting limitations like these disproportionately affect our minority communities. Our nation has a long history of disenfranchising people of color. The Voting Rights Act helped address that
column5: but there is still work to do. #HR1 (6/)"
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "Our laws create unnecessary burdens. In OK
column5: we require a notary on all absentee ballots. Our state has no history of absentee ballot fraud. In other states
column6: punishments don\u2019t fit crimes; laws revoke the right to vote even after sentences are completed. #HR1 (5/)"
column29: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "I just got back from the Congressional Civil Rights Pilgrimage
column5: where we toured some of the most pivotal sites in our nation\u2019s civil rights history. People there died for their right to vote
column6: but there are still Americans who lack this access. #HR1 (4/)"
column29: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "Here is a highlight of what I think is most important. It makes registering to vote easier. It ensures our elections are more secure. It shines a light on outside groups and their money in Washington. And it ensures you pick us
column28: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics

column4: "full_text": "There is literally nothing more important that we can and should do than ensuring our democracy is protected. The foundation of everything we do \u2013 national security
column6: everything \u2013 is our democratic system. We have to make sure every single citizen has a voice. #HR1 (2/)"
column29: chairwoman of the House Subcommittee on Space and Aeronautics
